12/03/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Osman Koruturk, Turkey's special representative to Iraq, said Thursday (11 March) that Turkey and the United States have agreed to continue dialogue about the future of Iraq. 
He spoke after a meeting with Ron Neumann, US foreign relations director of the Coalition Provisional Authority (CPA) in Iraq. 
They discussed the interim constitution adopted by the Iraqi Governing Council earlier this week and exchanged views on the performance of the interim government. 
Neumann said the goal of his visit to Turkey was to boost economic and cultural relations between Turkey and Iraq. 
He reiterated the CPA's commitment to maintaining Iraq's territorial integrity. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 11/03/04)
